[Uniqueness of cylindrical blow-ups]\label{t:main}
Let $p\in \mathbb N\setminus \{0,1,2\}$ and $\mathbf{C}_0$ be as in Assumption \ref{ass:cone}. There are constants $\bar \eta>0$ and $C$ depending only on $p,m,n$, and $\mathbf{C}_0$ with the following property. If $T, \Sigma, \Omega$ and $q$ are as in Assumption \ref{ass:cone} with $\eta=\bar \eta$,
then the tangent cone $\mathbf{C}$ to $T$ at $q$ is unique, has $(m-1)$-dimensional spine, and moreover the following decay estimates hold for every radius $r\leq 1$
    \begin{equation}\label{e:decay-always}
    \frac{1}{r^{m+2}}\int_{\mathbf{B}_r (q)}\mathrm{dist}^2(\bar q - q, \mathrm{spt}(\mathbf{C})) \, d\|T\| (\bar q) \leq C\, (\mathbf{E}_0 + \mathbf{A}^{1/2}) r^{\frac{1}{2}} \, ,
    \end{equation}
    \begin{equation}\label{e:decay-flat}
    \hat\mathscr{F}^p_{\mathbf{B}_1} ((\eta_{q,r})_\sharp T - \mathbf{C}) \leq C (\mathbf{E}_0^{1/2}+\mathbf{A}^{1/4}) r^\frac{1}{4}\, .
    \end{equation}
    In particular $\hat\mathscr{F}^p_{\mathbf{B}_1} (\mathbf{C}-\mathbf{C}_0) \leq C (\mathbf{E}_0^{1/2}+\mathbf{A}^{1/4}) + \bar\eta$.

