semantic_equivalence_artifact.original_latex_theorem:
\label{lem:structure_cones}
	Let $p \geq 2$ be an integer, and let $\mathbf{C}$ be an $m$-dimensional area minimizing cone ${\rm mod}(p)$ in $\mathbb{R}^{m+n}$ with spine $V$ of dimension $m-1$. Let $V^\perp$ be the orthogonal complement of $V$. Then:
	\begin{itemize}
		\item[(i)] $\mathbf{C} = \mathbf{C}' \times \left\llbracket{V}\right\rrbracket $ for some $1$-dimensional area minimizing cone ${\rm mod}(p)$ in $V^\perp$ (where we assume to have fixed a choice of a constant orientation $\vec{\tau}$ on $V$);
		\item[(ii)] There exist $N\geq 3$ distinct vectors $v(1), \ldots, v(N)\in \mathbb{S}^n \subset V^\perp$ and $N$ positive integers $\kappa(1), \ldots, \kappa(N) \in \left[1,\sfrac{p}{2}\right) \cap \mathbb{Z}$ such that
		\begin{itemize}
			\item[•] if $\ell(i) := \{t \,v(i) : t\geq 0\} \subset V^\perp$ is oriented in such a way that $\partial \left\llbracket{\ell(i)}\right\rrbracket = - \left\llbracket{0}\right\rrbracket$, then either $\mathbf{C}' = \sum_{i=1}^N \kappa(i) \left\llbracket{\ell(i)}\right\rrbracket $ or $\mathbf{C}' =
			- \sum_{i=1}^N \kappa(i) \left\llbracket{\ell(i)}\right\rrbracket$;
			\item[•] $\sum_{i=1}^N \kappa(i) v(i) = 0$. 
		\end{itemize}
	\item[(iii)] $\sum_{i=1}^N \kappa(i) = p$, and hence the $m$-dimensional density of $\mathbf{C}$ at $0$ is $\Theta_{\mathbf{C}}(0) = \frac{p}{2}$.
	\end{itemize}
	Moreover, when $ p$ is odd, the set of area minimizing cones ${\rm mod}(p)$ with spine of dimension $m-1$ is compact with respect to the flat topology.

